      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINI MINION (2) has some solid form under her belt and proved too classy last time to win by 2.75 lengths at Ballarat in a handy 22.42 beating Paw Cheyenne. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Looks the testing material. BROADWAY ICON (6) has some solid form under her belt and proved too strong last time to win by one length at this track in a handy 22.69 beating Frank Grimes. Boasts two wins from five starts out of this box. Can make it back-to-back wins. SUGAR SHINE (1) has been hard to follow lately, running fourth (22.96) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at this track. Can improve sharply here. TWILIGHT SLEUTH (3) should be thereabouts after filling a top-three at this track and distance most recently.",
